{#
  ============================================================================
  TEMPLATE: provider-as-laboratory_fsh.twig
  ============================================================================
  PURPOSE
    Generates TWO FSH instances that model a laboratory acting as a healthcare
    provider — specifically as the legal attester of a laboratory report within
    the SYNDERAI pipeline:

      1. PractitionerRole  — labels the laboratory as a provider role.
      2. Practitioner      — a placeholder laboratory practitioner.

    This template is a deliberately simplified stub ("FAKE ADD ONS") with
    hardcoded data representing a fictitious laboratory ("Laboratoire Central
    Européenne" in Brussels). It is intended as a structural placeholder until
    dynamic laboratory provider data is available in the pipeline.

  ⚠  STUB / PLACEHOLDER STATUS
    All Practitioner data in this template is hardcoded:
      Name    : Dr Ex Ample
      Address : Boulevard du Jardin Botanique 32, 1000 Brussels, Belgium
    The PractitionerRole similarly carries no dynamic content beyond the
    instance id. When real laboratory data becomes available, the hardcoded
    fields should be replaced with variable interpolation following the
    pattern used in provider-as-hospital_fsh.twig.

  PROFILE CONFORMANCE
    PractitionerRole : PractitionerRoleEu  (not the EuCore variant)
    Practitioner     : PractitionerEu      (not the EuCore variant)
    Note: the non-Core EU profiles are used here. These are the IHE XpandH /
    HL7 Europe EU lab profiles rather than the IPS EU Core profiles.

  NO ORGANISATION INSTANCE
    Unlike provider-as-hospital_fsh.twig, this template does not generate an
    Organization instance. The laboratory organisation is represented only
    through the address lines on the Practitioner and the narrative text of
    the PractitionerRole. An Organisation instance should be added when the
    template is promoted from stub to production.

  NO setInstance() CALLS
    Instance ids are interpolated directly into the `Instance:` keyword line.
    None of the instance names are registered in the `twigit()` return array.

  NO HTML OUTPUT
    Both %%HEAD%% and %%HTML%% sections are intentionally left empty.
    Each FSH instance carries only a minimal plain-text `text.div` narrative.

  PRACTITIONER IDENTIFIER
    A fresh UUID v4 is generated at render time via `getUUID()` and used as
    the practitioner identifier value under the HL7 Europe OID namespace
    (`HL7EUROPEEXAMPLESOID`). This UUID is ephemeral — it is not tracked
    across renders.

  CONTEXT VARIABLES
  ┌──────────────────────────────────────┬──────────┬────────────────────────────────────────┐
  │ Variable                             │ Type     │ Description                            │
  ├──────────────────────────────────────┼──────────┼────────────────────────────────────────┤
  │ laboratory.instancerole              │ string   │ UUID / id for the PractitionerRole     │
  │                                      │          │ resource; interpolated directly into   │
  │                                      │          │ the Instance: line.                    │
  │ laboratory.instancepractitioner      │ string   │ UUID / id for the Practitioner         │
  │                                      │          │ resource.                              │
  └──────────────────────────────────────┴──────────┴────────────────────────────────────────┘

  GLOBAL VARIABLES USED
    HL7EUROPEEXAMPLESOID — OID root for the practitioner identifier system URI:
                           "urn:oid:<HL7EUROPEEXAMPLESOID>"

  AUTHOR   KH
  SINCE    2025-09-14
  ============================================================================
#}

%%FSH%% {# ── Section marker required by the FSH pre-processor ─────────────── #}

{# ⚠ FAKE ADD ONS — stub instances for the laboratory organisation and legal attester #}

{#
  ── Instance 1: PractitionerRole ────────────────────────────────────────────
  Binds the practitioner to their role. Note: no organisation reference is
  included — the Organization instance is omitted from this stub template.
  Note: Instance id is interpolated directly — setInstance() is not called.
#}
Instance: Instance-PractitionerRole-{{ laboratory.instancerole }}
InstanceOf: PractitionerRoleEu
Usage: #inline
* id = "{{ laboratory.instancerole }}"
* practitioner = Reference(urn:uuid:{{ laboratory.instancepractitioner }})
{# Minimal narrative — dynamic content limited to the role id #}
* text.status = #generated
* text.div = """
<div xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">
Laboratory Role Id: {{ laboratory.instancerole }}
</div>
"""

{#
  ── Instance 2: Practitioner ────────────────────────────────────────────────
  Placeholder laboratory practitioner with fully hardcoded name and address.
  A fresh UUID is generated for the identifier value at render time.

  ⚠  All fields below are hardcoded stubs. Replace with variable interpolation
     (following provider-as-hospital_fsh.twig) when real data is available:
       name   : "dr Ex Ample"       → dynamic practitioner name fields
       address: Brussels stub       → dynamic laboratory address fields
#}
Instance: Instance-Practitioner-{{ laboratory.instancepractitioner }}
InstanceOf: PractitionerEu
Usage: #inline
* id = "{{ laboratory.instancepractitioner }}"

{# Practitioner identifier under the HL7 Europe OID namespace #}
* identifier.system = "urn:oid:{{ HL7EUROPEEXAMPLESOID }}"
{% set practitioneridentifier = getUUID() %} {# Generate ephemeral UUID for this identifier #}
* identifier.value = "{{ practitioneridentifier }}"
* identifier.assigner.display = "HL7 Europe"

{# Hardcoded stub name — to be replaced with dynamic values #}
* name.prefix = "dr"
* name.given[+] = "Ex"
* name.family = "Ample"

{# Hardcoded stub address — fictitious Brussels laboratory location #}
* address.line[+] = "Laboratoire Central Européenne"
* address.line[+] = "Boulevard du Jardin Botanique 32"
* address.postalCode = "1000"
* address.city = "Brussels"
* address.country = "Belgium"

{# Narrative reflects the hardcoded address #}
* text.status = #generated
* text.div = """
<div xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">
Laboratory: Laboratoire Central Européenne, 1000 Brussels, Belgium
</div>
"""

{# ⚠ END FAKE ADD ONS #}

%%HEAD%% {# ── Section marker required by the FSH pre-processor ─────────────── #}
{# No HEAD output — this template produces no HTML table. #}

%%HTML%% {# ── Section marker required by the FSH pre-processor ─────────────── #}
{# No HTML output — this template produces no HTML table. #}
